📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `m2400w` command is used to control and manage wireless (Wi-Fi) connections on your system. You can scan for Wi-Fi networks, connect to them, and view connection information.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `m2400w scan` --> 📡 Scan for available Wi-Fi networks.
    🔹 `m2400w connect <network-name>` --> 🔗 Connect to a Wi-Fi network with the specified name.  You will be prompted for the password.
    🔹 `m2400w disconnect` --> ✂️ Disconnect from the current Wi-Fi network.
    🔹 `m2400w status` --> ℹ️ Display information about the current connection (network name, signal strength, IP address, etc.).
    🔹 `m2400w save <network-name>` --> 💾 Save the password for a network for easier future connections.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ m2400w scan

    🔹 Scan for nearby Wi-Fi networks.

    $ m2400w connect MyHomeWifi

    🔹 Connect to the "MyHomeWifi" network.  The command will prompt for the password.

    $ m2400w status

    🔹 Display current connection information.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ m2400w disconnect

    🔹 Disconnects from the current Wi-Fi network.  After this, `m2400w status` will likely show no connection information.

